##A real-life account of the war-epidemic roadshow: How 9 new consumer entrepreneurs look for opportunities in crisis

Micro-signal, Rancaijing

A feature presentation, a daily in depth report, redefines the innovation economy.

By suki

Editor | Wei Jia

The consumer sector has been hit hard by the outbreak.

Restaurants, tourism, retail, cinemas and other offline businesses were the first to be affected. Many enterprises had to make layoffs because of the "cash flow" problem. On the other hand, new Consumer sectors such as fresh-air e-commerce, home service and unmanned retail containers also saw counter-trend growth and new opportunities.

The more we are in the midst of a major crisis, the more we look for opportunities in the midst of crisis. In order to build a bridge between entrepreneurs and investors, the Digital Economy Investment and financing alliance and Beijing Fund Town co-hosted by "looking for Chinese entrepreneurs" , jointly sponsored by 29 well-known investment institutions, the "Battle of the flu line roadshow" was officially launched on February 16. As of the morning of February 27,12 days, attracted 611 start-ups, 171 investment institutions to participate. The 29 investment institutions, which have participated in two roadshows on online education and new consumption, have a total fund size of 211.77 billion RMB under their management. A total of 55 jury teams composed of partners, senior investors and experts have been sent out to look at the projects online.

The second stage of the "road show on the battle against epidemic diseases" is dedicated to new consumption, sentence is too long, please supply a shorter sentence.

After intense preparation, a total of 96 new consumer start-ups, including calf wine, Haifan High-Five parent-child swimming, Fini city, zhuge io, downstairs, Weiback, Weituo Technology, FamilyOut and Zanthoxylum Bungeanum, were selected to participate in the second online roadshow.

"Road show on the battle line of Epidemic Diseases" new consumption special show held

The "search for Chinese creators" contest has been held for five consecutive years. Since its launch in 2015, the competition has attracted more than 9,000 entries and 50"China makers of the year" have been selected, many of which have grown into UNICORNS or gone public successfully, become the main force of innovation economy and Wind Vane. As in previous years, the judges of the competition will grade each entrepreneurial project. The outstanding projects are expected to receive investment and support from the institutions. They will also go straight to this year's "looking for Chinese creators" competition, participate in the competition "2020 China maker" selection.

Calf wine

Zhang Zisheng, founder and CEO of veal liqueur

Project description: Beijing Wucai Xiaoniu Wine Technology Co. , Ltd. is a business service company which integrates product research and development, brand operation, marketing and sales of liquor and related products. Xiaoniu wine is a brand of high-quality white liquor.

Core competence: Relying on the advantages of intelligent data, supply chain management and finance, the company builds a new retail platform in the vertical field of alcohol, and uses Saas Technology to provide business services for its partners and carry out digital transformation.

Stage of Development / Valuation: Angel Round / undisclosed

Operating status: nearly one million bottles of veal were sold in 2019, with sales reaching tens of millions.

Answers to the judges'questions

TIANTU investment partner Wei Guoxing: product positioning in what price range, the price of a single bottle of which liquor brand mark? What are the main value points of veal?

Zhang Zisheng, CEO and founder of Beijing Wucai Xiaoniu Wine Technology Co. , Ltd. : our current three mainstream wine pricing, 28 yuan is the target of the Niulanshan small wine, 36 yuan, 89 yuan is the target of the Niulanshan and Hongxing Erguotou.

The value point of the calf has three parts: First, our brand supplier Yongfeng County, with Red Star, Niulanshan, are three old state-owned brands, awareness and quality are no problem. Second, we use digital new retail model than the other two traditional play, more competitive, to meet the needs of today's young people, users and fans of the retention and fission will do better. Finally, the real core is that we use digital technology, a bottle of a code, can promise consumers 100% no fake wine.

Li Zhujie, founding partner of Bushi Venture Capital: Is Your Saas system used for selling wine, management or marketing? What's the connection?

Zhang Zisheng, CEO and founder of Beijing Colorful Calf Wine Technology Co. , Ltd. : If you sell wine in the traditional way, you must first find an agent, then a dealer, and then go to a liquor store to sell it, it takes a lot of salespeople to go to the front of the line and expand the market. With Saas, we can quickly integrate hotels into our platform. With Internet operations, good service for B segment customers, and only three people in the background can manage 300 stores, and then he can help the dealer manage his store.

B End Users can order directly on the system, there are 892 b end users, can also help B end users to C end users. The SAAS system, in addition to helping businesses sell veal, will also help them sell everything in the store, increase their exposure and customer acquisition without incurring too much cost, and even better retain users on our platform.

Haifan Parent Child Swimming Founder Wu Jing: The family box is a children's complex, we are doing a parent child swimming single field. Our model is similar to early childhood education, and the whole business model is similar to them, but we're much older. Yingnuo Angel Fund Partner Sheng Wang: In your cost structure, the cost of rent water and electricity is very low. Where is the general location of your large shop? Do you make money from rent or from the main business?

Wu Jing, founder of Haifan Parent Child Swimming: We have community stores and shopping malls, and take the second Tier City of Taiyuan as an example, the rental cost of both types of stores is less than two yuan per square meter per day. Our franchise, or second-tier cities, for example, our control is not more than three per square meter per day. Our main profit is still in the course revenue.

Liu Bo, Qingliu capital partner: How is the Operation Status of the Franchisee Now?

We don't know when the epidemic will end, so based on zero revenue in the first half of this year, overall revenue this year may not be much higher than last year, said Wu Jing, founder of Haifan parent child swimming. We are now more than 80% of franchisees in profit, net profit in more than 15% . In 2018, our turnover was around 22 million, and our net profit was around 7 million. In 2019, our revenue increased by nearly 50% .

Stage of Development / Valuation: Undisclosed

Bai Bertelsmann, Managing Director of Asia Investment Fund: What is the variable between your forecast of higher gross profit and net profit in 2020?

Until 2019, we are still in the campaign, this year we will start to explore the development of c-end products, the future c-end products to contribute to the profits will be a big variable.

Judges: WHAT'S THE COST MODEL for 23 million dollars in 2019?

We did four big Fini cities in 2019 and more than 30 small Fini cities, said Zheng Shengjie, Co founder and CEO of Fini City. The cost of small activities is mainly the depreciation and amortization of goods, the wages of operators on the spot, the rent of the site, and the labor cost of the transportation and erection fees. Large-scale events space is very large, usually is the choice of exhibition hall, the cost includes venue rental, promotion costs, ticket distribution channels, as well as operating and installation of staff costs.

Shokatsu. Io

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Shokatsu, founder and CEO of IO

Project Profile: Shokatsu built a complete service architecture from pre sales to after sales, around business scenarios that provide companies with out of the box user behavior analysis tools like Saas  , a privatized PaaS platform, and SMART data center services.

Core Competitiveness: The company launched a new generation of data analysis products, to provide enterprises with "product + service" data solutions, 5 years of industry experience, mature technology, complete service system. Core team from Spain Telecom, Oracle, SAP, Microsoft and other well-known enterprises at home and abroad.

Stage of Development / Valuation: Strategic Financing / UNDISCLOSED (completed)

Operating status: Since 2015, more than 60,000 enterprises have cooperated with us, serving customers in various industries.

Wang Cunfu, general manager of Investment and Research Department of China Internet Investment Corporation: Can you introduce the financial operation data?

We've raised money every year since 2016, and we've raised money recently, said Shokatsu, io's founder and CEO. Our company's strategy is to pursue revenue growth from early on, slowly from loss to now level off, the whole of 2019 is basically in cash flow balance, a small loss, to this year is expected to start full-year revenue will be profitable.

Perplexed Venture Capital Liu Fangjun: Which Industries do these customers focus on? How long does it take to deliver a data center product to a customer?

Shokatsu, founder and CEO of IO, said: the Data Center and Taiwan are currently focused on the retail and real estate sectors. For Saas and privatization, we will focus on different industries in different economic environments.

In 2019, it's more finance, in 2018, it's education, in 2017, it's mutual funds, it was Internet companies at the beginning, so our corresponding industries are relatively less concentrated. We've also been doing a lot of product customization lately, lowering the bar a bit. But GM has the advantage that, like during the recent outbreak, customers are still growing in some industries, such as gaming and pharmaceuticals.

Because the platform is not a standardized product, and because the data product itself needs data to land, it needs to have a business status before it can operate. We usually talk about the budget for the second year at the end of the year. The year will be divided into 3-4 phases, one phase per quarter.

It's downstairs

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Downstairs, founder and CEO Zhang Ying

PROJECT DESCRIPTION: The company takes the self-developed unmanned convenience cabinet as the intelligent terminal, through the Internet big data management system and the automation technology innovation, Constructs the thorough city community "public refrigerator" , and to operate a high-quality supply chain to provide 24/7, fresh and efficient community retail services.

Core Competitiveness: The team started a new business downstairs, with long-accumulated supply chain advantages and community operating advantages, has now landed in more than 400 communities in Beijing, and Haidilao semi-finished food cooperation, Improve Ping efficiency.

Development stagefinancing: A + round $10 million

Operating status: Front end earnings in April 2019. Currently focused on Beijing and Shanghai health rapid expansion, Beijing into 400 communities a total of 1,600 machines. In the future, downstairs will be extended to the whole country, committed to becoming the first platform of intelligent retail community in China.

Zhao Jing, vice president, lightspeed China: Is there competition between convenience store and home store formats?

Downstairs, founder and CEO Zhang Ying: When you get home, the delivery guy will send you a bottle of milk, and the delivery fee will be at least three yuan. If you use a convenient counter to fulfill your contract, it will only cost 15 cents, including all the hardware, software, depreciation and maintenance costs. A bottle of 500 ML fresh milk is now only 9.90 yuan. When the unit price is not high, you also want to get fresh milk, and you also want it to be convenient and safe. Refrigeration is the most suitable way to keep the contract in the downstairs convenience cabinet, the cost of performance is low. Our break-even point is very low, 600 yuan on it, the average return cycle is 12-15 months.

Smell BACK

Wang Zhixiang, founder of Weiback

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Project description: through data-based products, market-based taste upgrades, health attributes added value, fashion product packaging, to create a series of modern young people to meet the consumer needs of local snack Boutique, in a number of mainstream e-commerce platform to become a star sales, was called the "light of domestic snacks. ".

Core Competitiveness: The Hong kong-style salted egg yolk fish skin, the daily sales of more than 10,000 copies, the next month to buy 28% , the next month online sales of up to 2 million. There are seasonal explosion of the southern Fujian Round Moon Cakes, 30 days to sell 100,000 copies.

Stage of Development / Financing: Pre-a Round / Tens of millions of dollars

Operational status: 2019 laying of the online platform 300 + , laying of the offline outlets 1W + . The company hopes to launch a 5-10 explosion in 2021, with online platforms expanding to 1000 + , offline outlets rolling out to 10W + , and overseas distributors adding up to 1000 + .

TIANTU investment partner Wei Guoxing: during the epidemic, Wei BACK sales?

Wang Zhixiang, founder of Weiback: Instead, our sales market is growing. As a result of the epidemic, our sales in February were double that of last year, but the goods could not be sent out. There are still some problems in the whole logistics chain and the distribution chain in the middle. There are many customers because of non-receipt of goods led to return goods, we are now in the discretion to reduce the new event schedule, because soon to March 8th, we will be more worried about the issue of shipping.

Liu Bo, Qingliu capital partner: Can you specify the current channel situation, as well as the situation of gross profit?

Wei Back founder Wang Zhixiang: we now have 80% of direct retail, to the C end, 20% in the form of wholesale distribution. 80% of that comes online and 20% offline. Our own relatively high gross margin, product gross margin of 65% , to the offline distribution of Mori relatively low, at about 50% .

Perplexed venture founding partner Li Zhujie: So many snacks can be done, why choose fish skin this category?

Wei Back founder Wang Zhixiang: The fish skin category is because in our in-depth research results, the number of puffed snacks shipped is the highest, after Candy, candy itself is a down market, we are very optimistic about expanding such a small growth market.

Based on this choice, puffed food upgrade has two directions, one is the process upgrade, with low-temperature frying or freeze-drying process to replace the original high-temperature frying process. On the other hand, raw materials have been upgraded to replace Rice cracker with yams, corn, and sweet potatoes. After testing, no matter how the process is upgraded, there is no way to retain the crisp taste of puffed food. As for the raw materials, many merchants are also making yams, but none of this solves the problem of consumers'mental perception of the concept of healthy food.

We think of protein, in 2018, fish skin in Singapore has been relatively popular in the local market, one after another to the domestic market, and Singapore Fish Skin factory in Dongguan, Guangdong, is actually a local product, we began to pay attention to this track. Consumers in Guangdong and Hong Kong have also become our specific seed users.

WITWER technologies

Zhu Qi, founder and CEO of Vit

PROJECT DESCRIPTION: Vitol Technology is a Data Center provider that provides live streaming services and related supply chain services. It has two main products: live eye and broadcast hub. Live eye data products optimizes the efficiency and effectiveness of the live broadcast organization / supply chain by collecting the public data of the whole network every day, including 160,000 + Live studio and 10 million SKU products. Brand Pool can help the brand to monitor and analyze the data of live stream, interaction and transformation, control the price, goodwill and sales trend of the goods, and realize the intelligent match between the goods and the anchorperson.

Core competency: Big Data and AI to help users make decisions when launching talent, and to help them do the shop live generation operation. Product Broadcast Remit customers include Bao Zun, orange, Le Qi, Nestle, Levis, HACCI, healthcare, Omron and so on.

Wang Cunfu, general manager of Investment and Research Department of China Netcom: What is the profit model of Witto? Is there any privacy or other issue with this kind of access to data that is publicly captured on the web?

We are a data platform, mainly presenting data, but at the same time we have a business collaboration tool, which is biased towards Saas, but we don't charge for either for the time being, the paid part is mainly in the product broadcast remit solution and future S2B to make a profit. We now publicly collect two hundred thousand live rooms, all of which collect public data, not decrypted or obtained in any illegal way, nor any personal data.

Wang Daoping, partner of Huachuang capital: What are your main rivals? How's the income?

Zhu Qi, founder and CEO of witto Technologies, said: We have a relatively small number of competitors in each module, but the overall business model is different, for example in the area of live source data, we started in 2018 with a few data companies. There's competition for brand store solutions like product exchange, but unlike our approach, we're more about providing a data driven solution: by combining our data, do a set of brand launch consulting and shop generation operation, data also for us to provide a barrier to this part of the business.

There is no competing product that is exactly the same as our overall business model. For example, one of our large brand customers, through our brand live solutions, has a 1:40 total input to output ratio. From October to December last year, we made close to a million dollars a month, mainly for the service fee of PTT.

Same question

Selling cars and luxury goods can also be converted to growing grass online

1, offline consumption by the impact of the epidemic, almost overnight "do wechat business" , which types of projects suitable for online, which is not suitable? What are the difficulties in the process of the transformation line? Can you give some suggestions?

Yingnuo Angel Fund Partner Sheng Wang: score two dimensions to see. The first dimension is the online category that directly drives sales. It should be a physical commodity, where the speed of consumer decision-making is relatively fast and the cost of decision-making is relatively low. In other words, things can not be too expensive, nor can they be too complicated, and they can be relatively close to user needs. In fact, they are some everyday consumer goods, it's perfect for going online. Because now the live streaming of e-commerce with more and more ability to carry goods, this epidemic also makes everyone more and more acceptable.

On the other hand, for some heavy decision-making or service products, for example, during the epidemic, there were many people who tried to sell cars and luxury goods online. The original delivery and performance scenarios for such products were offline, can also be converted to online grass. It is not a bad thing for enterprises to plant more grass for customers with their products and brands. This will at least attract some attention, access to some private sector traffic, can help in the future conversion of customers.

Song Xiaofei, vice general manager of Shanshui venture capital, said the epidemic may speed up the "non-contact economy" of online scenes including E-commerce, live broadcasts, short videos, Games, and knowledge payments. In addition, the entity retail industry is trying to survive the epidemic, more urgent to try to transfer line, sub-categories such as maternal and infant supplies, cosmetics, consumer goods, clothing and hats, fresh food, household appliances and so on will continue to accelerate online, e-commerce. Such as tourism, catering, entertainment, culture, sports and other experiential offline scene consumption industry, affected by the epidemic has been greatly cooled, and unable or difficult to transform online, after the epidemic will be restored to life.

Home Service, no one retail to welcome the good

2. Apart from connecting online, what are some of the ways companies can try now?

Yingnuo Angel Fund partner Wang Sheng: Now during the epidemic everyone can not go out, the most important is home service, this direction or can be more development. In addition, no one retail will produce a Poli, Lazio good because of this outbreak. If you have an unmanned retail container downstairs, the range is relatively diverse, in addition to food and beverages, there will be some fresh fruits and vegetables, and even medical supplies, it will feel very convenient.

After the outbreak of food and beverage industry is expected to recover quickly, tourism to a small climax

3. Will there be a wave of retaliatory spending after the epidemic is over? Offline, online should be how to meet this wave of consumption tide?

Wang Daoping, partner of Huachuang capital: It depends on different industries. For example, food and beverage may recover relatively quickly. Three Meals a Day is just needed, but it is difficult to retaliate for consumption, because it is difficult to overconsume, and it is estimated that it will recover relatively quickly to normal levels, hotels and some service industries are also expected to recover slowly, and travel is likely to have a small upsurge as trips during the Spring Festival are held back and released after the outbreak. For the faster recovery of the industry, each company's corresponding marketing and operation activities are expected to be more and more concentrated, enterprises can do some plans according to their own circumstances, how to better and more efficient work, to avoid direct competition.

Song Xiaofei, vice general manager of Shanshui Venture Capital: In the short term, there will be some recovery rebound in the consumption industry, after all, these are a part of people's lives. But the stage of income reduction will also affect the epidemic after the consumption, some families, young groups are in debt, coupled with the psychological repair of consumers still need a process, consumption will be more cautious. In the medium to long term, a significant proportion of the population will not blindly consume, will only pay more attention to the health consumption. Some consumption scenarios such as eating out, gathering, and so on will be greatly reduced. Store bought recovery is still a process. All of these changes will affect post-epidemic consumption to some extent.

It's hard to compete with a simple no-man's-shop player

4. Last year, no one in the community convenience store development slowed down, under the epidemic can regain new opportunities? Some of the unmanned community stores are starting to work with semi-finished dishes. Do you like this model? What types of data do you focus on when looking at these types of projects?

Wang Daoping, a partner at Huachuang capital, said: No one's convenience stores have received a lot of attention under the epidemic. From the perspective of consumer convenience, this is also a good form. We believe that more companies will try to enter the market. I think it's hard to compete with a simple no-man's-shop player, and a big platform and company would give you an edge.

Ying Nuo Angel Fund Partner Sheng Wang: pure no one convenience store in the short term we are not particularly optimistic, when looking at these models, the main look is Sku, movable sales, inventory turnover and other models. On the other hand is the focus on efficiency, the distribution of points, whether there is a pre-warehouse, logistics, replenishment efficiency, as well as the stability of equipment, whether convenient maintenance.

Chao shoes, Hanfu the biggest pain point in the supply chain

5. Last year, the rise of new consumption trends such as Guochao, Chaowan, Chaowan and Hanfu. What new challenges will we face this year? What are some good ideas for expansion, operations, etc. ?

Sheng Wang, a partner at Innolux Angel Fund, said: These are irreversible trends that have evolved over time from our consumer base. In sneaker's case, however, I was slightly concerned. In the past, sneaker had a loyal following, and was willing to spend and use it, but in the last two years, the spike in the sneaker market has been driven more by selling shoes. And I think that shoe flipping actually drove sneaker away from the real value of the merchandise. I think this is going to be a very challenging market this year, and I don't think this year or even next year is going to surpass last year's surge.

Among the above trends, I think the most painful link is the supply chain, especially on Hanfu. The supply chain is particularly painful. If this problem is not solved properly, it will inevitably affect the speed of industrial development. Although user demand is very strong, the supply chain can not keep up, design ability and product quality can not keep up, it will be very dangerous, must be strengthened.

The retail upgrade, health food, insurance and so on of low-level crowd store new machine

6. What are the new demographics and trends in consumption that deserve attention in 2020? Have you seen any exciting projects lately?

Wang Daoping, partner of Huachuang capital: We pay more attention to the retail upgrading of low-line people. In addition, we also pay more attention to the trend of accelerating the integration of online and offline, as well as new distinctive brands. For example, we invest in Super Zero, is the field of meal generation is a very distinctive brand, product and marketing are very distinctive.

Song Xiaofei, vice general manager of Shanshui Venture Capital, said: After the epidemic, people will focus on creating a healthy home environment and investing in personal health, and there will be great opportunities for people to change their health spending habits. Online consultation, telemedicine, medicine O2o, the Internet medical enterprise ushered in the ring of opportunities.

Liu Bo, Qingliu capital partner: The four subsectors may benefit. One is the convenience of short-term preservation, which can mean better health and taste. This outbreak is a great opportunity and promotion for more advanced short-term food products; the second category of beneficiaries is health food products. This outbreak is a compulsory university study of the concept of health for the whole population, the future health requirements for food will be more prominent; the third category is insurance, focusing on the type of health insurance, people will see a greater need for commercial health insurance in the future; and the fourth category is membership management system products. This wave of events has made many consumer companies realise the importance of running their own membership systems.
